### 1 Create a new user
POST http://localhost:8080/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "bob",
  "email": "bob@example.com"
}

### 2 List all users (-> shows bob)
GET http://localhost:8080/users

### 3 Create another user
POST http://localhost:8080/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "carla",
  "email": "carla@example.com"
}

### 4 List all users again (-> shows bob and carla)
GET http://localhost:8080/users

### 5 User 1 (bob) creates a new poll
POST http://localhost:8080/polls/bob
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "What is your favourite sport?",
  "validUntil": "2030-09-15T10:00:00Z",
  "options": [
    {"caption": "Soccer", "presentationOrder": 1},
    {"caption": "Volleyball", "presentationOrder": 2}
  ]
}

### 6 List polls (-> shows the new poll)
GET http://localhost:8080/polls

### 7 Add new vote option: Basketball
POST http://localhost:8080/polls/1/option
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "caption": "Basketball",
  "presentationOrder": 3
}

### 8 Add new vote option: Tennis
POST http://localhost:8080/polls/1/option
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "caption": "Tennis",
  "presentationOrder": 4
}

### 9 List all options of the poll (-> should show 4 options)
GET http://localhost:8080/polls/1

### 10 User 2 (carla) votes for tennis (option 4)
POST http://localhost:8080/votes/1/4/carla

### 11 User 1 (bob) votes for basketball (option 3)
POST http://localhost:8080/votes/1/3/bob

### 12 List votes from the poll (-> shows both votes)
GET http://localhost:8080/votes/1
